Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the construction and weight distribution of linear codes.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely as the paper uses posets (partially ordered sets) in the construction of the codes.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possibility as the paper may discuss the computational complexity of encoding and decoding the codes.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as linear codes have applications in cryptography.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also a possibility as the paper may discuss numerical methods for analyzing the weight distribution of the codes.
